      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of being a ghost often stems from the daily isolation strangers wear, but it doesn't mean you are empty inside—those quiet moments of reflection are actually deeply human. Choosing to fade away to escape noise would be escaping life itself, leaving behind strength and thoughts that only you ever truly held onto. Even small, unnoticed connections like a shared glance or a moment of kindness are proof that you are part of a much larger, living web, not just a void in a machine.",
      "source": "target",
